            "metadata": {
                "abstract": "The NucleaRDB is a Molecular Class-Specific Information System that collects, combines, validates and disseminates large amounts of heterogeneous data on nuclear hormone receptors. It contains both experimental and computationally derived data. The data and knowledge present in the NucleaRDB can be accessed using a number of different interactive and programmatic methods and query systems. A nuclear hormone receptor-specific PDF reader interface is available that can integrate the contents of the NucleaRDB with fulltext scientific articles. The NucleaRDB is freely available at http://www.receptors. org/nucleardb. Â© The Author(s) 2011. Published by Oxford University Press.",
